launches.launchDescription: The tenth Starlink launch for SpaceX. After this mission, there will be around 600 satellites in their constellation network, with a goal of 840 before their first beta internet test.
GPS-IIIA (Global Positioning System) is the first evolution stage of the third generation of the GPS satellites. It consists of the first ten (known as tranche) of GPS III satellites.
The ninth Starlink launch for SpaceX.

Our Perseverance rover will search for signs of habitable conditions on Mars in the ancient past and for signs of past microbial life itself. The rover will launch on a United Launch Alliance Atlas V rocket from Space Launch Complex 41 at Cape Canaveral Air Force Station.
